kool air conditioners became a separate national union electric division this company continued to produce radios television sets and phonographs distributed under the emerson and dumont names and hifi equipment under the pilot name between  and  the national union electric division lost about  million due to too little volume to cover costs the division contracted out the manufacturing of television sets and some other home entertainment products to admiral corp and laidoff  employees in addition to importing some of its home entertainment products from the far east emerson continued to be responsible for design engineering and marketing in late  national union electric announced that emerson was discontinuing distribution of television sets and other home entertainment products in  emerson sold its license for marketing products under the emerson name to major electronics corp founded in  by melvin lane and incorporated in  this brooklynbased company originally made childrens phonographs the company later diversified into the production and sale of a broad line of lowpriced home entertainment products that included stereos radios and clock radios in  major also began importing lowcost radios by  the company was only manufacturing portable phonographs in  the company moved its headquarters to secaucus new jersey and changed its name to emerson radio corp in  sales rose from  million in fiscal  to  million in fiscal  the year in which phonographs radios tape recorders and players compact stereos digital clock radios and other low to mediumpriced electronic equipment was being imported assembled and marketed primarily under the emerson name approximately  percent of its components were being imported from the far east and  percent from each great britain and domestically and assembled in either secaucus or sun valley california in  emerson began selling heart aid after purchasing a large portion of cardiac resuscitator corp a nearbankrupt company emerson spent heavil