 sales slump for phonograph music that accompanied the postworld war i recession and the growth of commercial radio it went from the selfclaimed third largest record manufacturer into receivership –edit in  emerson phonograph co passed into the hands of benjamin abrams  and rudolph kanarak abrams a phonograph and record salesman along with his two brothers ran the company and renamed it emerson radio  phonograph corp in  after entering the radio business the companys record interests were subsequently sold although emerson introduced the first radiophonograph combination sold in the united states the company remained in obscurity until  when during the great depression it introduced the peewee radio see historical products below –edit emerson radio  phonograph converted to military production for world war ii in  when it held onesixth of the us radio market in  it became a public corporation when it offered over  percent of its stock to the public for  a share in  among its first postwar products emerson offered a television set with a inch tube although its ending retail price was nearly equal to a months salary for the average working american it put emerson at the lower end of the market however between fiscal  and  the high demand for television allowed emerson to more than double its sales its net income reached a record of  million in fiscal  with sales of  million –edit in  emerson radio and phonograph purchased quiet heet corp which entered the company into air conditioning although radio represented only  percent of emersons revenue by  the company credited itself as creating the firsts of the clock radio selfpowered radio and transistorized pocket radio production of tape recorders began in  emerson radio and phonograph paid  million to purchase the consumer products division of dumont laboratories in  with this acquisition a higherpriced line of television sets phonographs and highfidelity and stereo instruments along with the dumont trademark was added t