ets and licenses many product lines worldwide including products sold and sometimes licensed under the brand name g clef a homage to emersons logo contents  history  –  –  –  –  –  –  –  –present  products  consumer electronics  hd radio  smartset  historical products  references  external links historyedit –edit emerson radio corp was incorporated in  as emerson phonograph co naics  consumer electronics wholesaling based in new york city by an early recording engineer and executive victor hugo emerson who was at one time employed by columbia records the first factories were opened in chicago and boston in  in december of that year the company fell victim to the sales slump for phonograph music that accompanied the postworld war i recession and the growth of commercial radio it went from the selfclaimed third largest record manufacturer into receivership –edit in  emerson phonograph co passed into the hands of benjamin abrams  and rudolph kanarak abrams a phonograph and record salesman along with his two brothers ran the company and renamed it emerson radio  phonograph corp in  after entering the radio business the companys record interests were subsequently sold although emerson introduced the first radiophonograph combination sold in the united states the company remained in obscurity until  when during the great depression it introduced the peewee radio see historical products below –edit emerson radio  phonograph converted to military production for world war ii in  when it held onesixth of the us radio market in  it became a public corporation when it offered over  percent of its stock to the public for  a share in  among its first postwar products emerson offered a television set with a inch tube although its ending retail price was nearly equal to a months salary for the average working american it put emerson at the lower end of the market however between fiscal  and  the high demand for television allowed emerson to more than double its sales its net income reached a record of  million in fiscal  with sales of  million –edit in  emerson radio and phonograph purchased quiet heet corp which entered the company into air conditioning although radio represented only  percent of emersons revenue by  the company credited itself as creating the firsts of the clock radio selfpowered radio and transistorized pocket radio production of tape recorders began in  emerson radio and phonograph paid  million to purchase the consumer products division of dumont laboratories in  with this acquisition a higherpriced line of television sets phonographs and highfidelity and stereo instruments along with the dumont trademark was added to emersons products however by this time the us television market was saturated and many customers who were in need of another set were waiting for color television instead of buying a replacement sales fell from  million in fiscal  to  million in fiscal  when the company earned only  a costcutting campaign by abrams rebounded net income which reached  million in fiscal  on sales of  million in fiscal  emersons last full year of independent operation it earned  million on sales of  million –edit in  the company acquired the pilot radio corp from jerrold corp later in  emerson radio and phonograph was purchased for approximately  million in cash and stock by national union electric corp a diversified manufacturer its line of quiet kool air conditioners became a separate national union electric division this company continued to produce radios television sets and phonographs distributed under the emerson and dumont names and hifi equipment under the pilot name between  and  the national union electric division lost about  million due to too little volume to cover costs the division contracted out the manufacturing of television sets and some other home entertainment products to admiral corp and laidoff  employees in addition to importing some of its home entertainment products from the far east emerson continued to be responsible for design engineering and marketing in late  national union electric announced that emerson was discontinuing distribution of television sets and other home entertainment products in  emerson sold its license for marketing products under the emerson name to major electronics corp founded in  by melvin lane and incorporated in  this brooklynbased company originally made childrens phonographs the company later diversified into the production and sale of a broad line of lowpriced home entertainment products that included stereos radios and clock radios in  major also began importing lowcost radios by  the company was only manufacturing portable phonographs in  the company moved its headquarters to secaucus new jersey and changed its name to emerson radio corp in  sales rose from  million in fiscal  to  million in fiscal  the year in which phonographs radios tape recorders and players compact stereos digital clock radios and other low to mediumpriced electronic equipment was being imported assembled and marketed primarily under the emerson name approximately  percent of its components were being imported from the far east and  percent from each great britain and domestically and assembled in either secaucus or sun valley california in  emerson began selling heart aid after purchasing a large portion of cardiac resuscitator corp a nearbankrupt company emerson spent heavily to develop and produce both an improved implantable cardioverterdefibrillator and a pacemaker in addition the company took an  percent share in a developer of computerized axial tomographic cat scanners because this line of products never made money emerson disposed of its holdings in them between  emerson radio dropped its last usmade product the phonograph line in  because it became unprofitable due to rising labor costs despite harsh competition emerson radio raised its sales and earnings in fiscal  to  million and  million respectively their plan was to have their suppliers mai